downloadHistory.py downloads all message history that is available to you up until 00:00 this morning.

Uses slack-history-export (https://github.com/hisabimbola/slack-history-export), install with:

    npm install slack-history-export

Get your slack token at:

    https://api.slack.com/custom-integrations/legacy-tokens


Run with
    python download_history.py <slack token> <outdir> [--exclude_channels]

It will start downloading as soon as any message is sent to any slack channel, group or direct message.
